<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 pt-20 pb-24">

  <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 mb-6">feedspec.org</h1>

  <div class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
    <p>Feeds power the open web — RSS, Atom, JSON Feed, AT Protocol — but the infrastructure around them has gaps. feedspec.org is where we publish open specifications to fill them.</p>

    <p>These specs extend existing feed formats, not replace them. They build on standards you already use (OAuth 2.0, JWT, well-known URIs) and degrade gracefully — readers that don't support them just see what they always have.</p>

    <p>This is a project by <a href="https://shellen.com" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600 transition-colors">Jason Shellen</a>. Specs are developed in the open on <a href="https://github.com/shellen/open-portable-entitlement" class="text-emerald-500 hover:text-emerald-600 transition-colors">GitHub</a>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-16 border-t border-zinc-900/5 pt-10">
    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-6">Specifications</h2>

